    <note>Yang(2) Xie [2003] His father served the Liu(2) rulers of Southern Han, then Song, first in Shenxi and last in Henan where Xie was buried. Chen(1)'s [7099] father, Jinglue's [2000] grandfather, Yi(3)'s [7097] nephew, Ding(1) Du's [1640] father-in-law. In 1077, a grandnephew, Jingfen [4039], was appointed as supervisor of tax media conversion in Huaixi circuit. Xie's younger brother, Ren [4046], died early and left a son named Xun [4045], who was Jingfen's father. Chao Buzhi, WJ, 64.5a; XCB, 118.1a, 1a-1b, 144.6a; Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 29.3a-5a. CBD, 4, 3118.</note>
